name: The World Peace Prize. Who's Getting the 100 Million Zeni?!
To the Promised Vacation! Vegeta Goes on a Family Trip?

description: Proper Japanese Title: 夢の続きはどこだ!? 超スーパーサイヤ人ゴッドを探せ! (Yume no tsuzuki wa doko da!? Sūpā Saiya-jin Goddo o sagase!)
name: Where Does the Dream Continue!? Search for Super Saiyan God!

description: Proper Japanese Title: 目指せドラゴンボール! ピラフ一味の大作戦! (Mezase Doragon Bōru! Pirafu ichimi no dai-sakusen!)
name: Aim for the Dragon Balls! The Pilaf Gang's Great Strategy!

description: Proper Japanese Title: 界王星の決戦! 悟空VS破壊神ビルス (Kaiō-sei no kessen! Gokū VS Hakaishin Birusu)
name: Decisive Battle on Kaiō's Planet! Goku vs. God of Destruction Beerus

description: Proper Japanese Title: 破壊神を怒らせるな! ドキドキ誕生パーティー (Hakaishin o okoraseru na! Doki-doki tanjō pātī)
name: Don’t Anger the God of Destruction! A Tense Birthday Party

description: Proper Japanese Title: よくもオレのブルマを! ベジータ怒りの突然変異!? (Yokumo ore no Buruma o! Bejīta ikari no totsuzenhen’i!?)
name: How Dare You Hit My Bulma! Vegeta’s Furious Transformation?!

description: Proper Japanese Title: 悟空見参! ビルス様からのラストチャンス!? (Gokū kenzan! Birusu-sama kara no rasuto chansu!?)
name: Goku Steps Up! Beerus-sama's Last Chance?!

description: Proper Japanese Title: お待たせ, ビルス様.　ついに超スーパーサイヤ人ゴッド誕生! (O matase, Birusu-sama. Tsuini Sūpā Saiya-jin Goddo tanjō!)
name: Sorry for Waiting, Beerus-sama! Finally, Super Saiyan God is Born!

description: Proper Japanese Title: 見せろ悟空! 超スーパーサイヤ人ゴッドの力パワー!! (Misero Gokū! Sūpā Saiya-jin Goddo no pawā!!)
name: Show me Goku! The Power of Super Saiyan God!

description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get Benson to stop watching cat videos.
name: Cat Videos

description: Muscle Man and High Five Ghost get struck by lightning and can't remember each other.
name: Struck By Lightning

description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help their friend Party Horse get back together with his girlfriend.
name: Return of the Party Horse

description: After staying up for two straight nights watching a movie marathon, Mordecai and Rigby have to get their sleep cycle back on track.
name: Sleep Cycle

description: Eph and Dutch work together to thwart the Master's greatest ally. Justine runs into trouble with the Mayor, while Setrakian tracks down the real owner of the Lumen.
name: The Assassin

description: Picking up months after the Singularity attacked Central City, Barry (Grant Gustin) is still struggling to forgive himself for Eddie's death. Concerned about putting his friends in danger, Barry has pushed everyone away and has chosen to protect the city on his own. When a meta-human named Atom Smasher (guest-star Adam Copeland) attacks the city, Iris (Candice Patton) tells Barry that he needs to let his friends help him protect the citizens of Central City. Meanwhile, Cisco (Carlos Valdes) helps Joe (Jesse L. Martin) with his Meta Task Force.
name: The Man Who Saved Central City

has_staff_review.name: The Flash Episode 201: "The Man Who Saved Central City"

deck: After months of a bliss filled getaway from the Arrow, Oliver and Felicity are called back to Star City in order to combt the 'Ghosts' led by Damien Darhk
description:
MY NAME IS THE GREEN ARROW

Oliver (Stephen Amell) and Felicity’s (Emily Bett Rickards) blissful getaway is cut short when Thea (Willa Holland) and Laurel (Katie Cassidy) pay them a visit and tell Oliver they need his help back in Star City. The city has been attacked by “Ghosts,” assassins led by a dangerous man named Damien Darhk (guest star Neal McDonough). However, when Oliver returns, Diggle (David Ramsey) makes it very clear that he doesn’t want Oliver on the team.

Thor Freudenthal directed the episode with story by Greg Berlanti & Beth Schwartz and teleplay by Marc Guggenheim & Wendy Mericle (#401).
name: Green Arrow

description: Dutch fights for her life against Eichhorst as Fet, Nora, and Eph frantically search the city for her. Setrakian confronts an old acquaintance on his search for the Occido Lumen, while Gus helps the Guptas escape across the border to safety.
name: Dead End

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺のかあちゃん (Ore no Kaa-chan)

Takeo's mother's due date is approaching, but she continues to engage in household chores with dangerous enthusiasm. She ridicules Takeo for being anxious for her well-being, but an unexpected incident causes her to evaluate her son.
name: My Mom

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺のチョコレート (Ore no Chokorēto)

Takeo is over the moon over his new little sister, Maki. With Valentine's Day approaching, Takeo's heart is set aflutter again since he has never gotten chocolates from a girl who liked him in his life. He can't wait to see what Yamato will give him, but...
name: My Chocolate

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 俺と手紙 (Ore to Tegami)

Every year, Suna has received an anonymous letter and chocolate on Valentine's Day. Every time, the letter says, "I don't need anything in return, but please like me." One day, Takeo senses a strange presence behind them, and meets the sender of the letter, Amami Yukika. After hearing about her longtime feelings for Suna, Takeo decides to help her!
name: The Letter and Me

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 素人 (Shirōto)

Sora and Shiro, a pair of anti social NEET gamer extraordinaires, suddenly find themselves in a new world where games decide every facet of life...something that they take to immediately.
name: Beginner

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 挑戦者 (Chōsensha)

Sora and Shiro's new friend Steph makes a foolish bet that ends with Sora the victor. As the new king of Elkia is crowned, Steph details the fall of the Imanity race and her desperate struggle to prove her father, the former king, right.
name: Challenger

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 熟練者 (Jukurensha)

With a new queen of Elkia abotu to be announced, Shiro steps in to take the reigns from her in the only way he know how: playing the game.
name: Expert

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 国王 (Kokuou)

A lively game of chess turns into something more, and after emerging victorious Shiro and Sora ascend up the tower of power once again.
name: Grandmaster

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 駒並べ (Komanarabe)

Sora and Shiro have vacated the palace and have elected to live in a rundown shack. Steph begins to fear that they are not the saviors she thought they were, and challenges them to a number of games of "chance".
name: Weak Square

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 一手 (Itte)

Sora and Shiro challenge the Flugel Jibril in an epic game of shiritori, with the knowledge of two worlds at stake.
name: Interesting

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 死に手 (Shinite)

Sora aims to challenge the mighty Warbeast empire, but soon learns that it may be a fruitless endeavor.
name: Sacrifice

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 起死回生 (Kishikaisei)

Sora, Shiro, Steph and Jibril make their way to the Warbeast embassy to challenge them with a risky plan with even riskier stakes.
name: Fake End

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 解離法 (Kairihō)

One is nothing without the other: Shiro is devastated from the disappearance of her Big bro. It's up to her, Steph and Jibril to figure out how to bring him back.
name: Sky Walk

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 指向法 (Shikōhō)

With Imanity at stake, Blank and their trusty sidekicks enter into a game with the Werebeasts, where an all too familiar city becomes the battleground...
name: Blue Rose

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 誘導法 (Yūdōhō)

Izuna, though powerful, has been matched in game play. This first person shooter will test their limits in virtual space. As tension flares, friendly fire becomes eminent.
name: Killing Giant

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ルール ナンバー 10 (Rūru Nanbā Jū)

Izuna's abilities seem to defy physics leaving Sora and Shiro only one option… Run!
name: Rule Number 10

description: The Turtles are baited by an unknown enemy into deadly traps.
name: The Fourfold Trap

description: When Raph makes a new friend in Zog, an alien Triceraton, he may have bitten off more than he can chew.
name: Dinosaur Seen in Sewers!

description: When the Turtles get word of the Kraang's return, they realize there is an even bigger threat coming to Earth!
name: Annihilation Earth, Part 1

description: Dr. Eggman is missing his particle accelerator and all evidence points to Sonic. With the villagers also claiming stolen items, Sonic must find the real thief in order to clear his name.
name: It Wasn't Me, It Was the One-Armed Hedgehog

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 十一号棟 弥生の看病 (Jū Ichi Gōtō Yayoi no Kanbyō)

Haruki is down with a cold, and the only one to help him out is Yayoi.
name: Building Eleven: How Yayoi Nurses?

description:
Proper Japanese Title: オレへの手紙 (Ore e no Tegami)

With help from Takeo and Yamato, Yukika finally manages to tell Sunakawa her feelings. Yukika takes it even a step further by inviting Suna to go on a date with her to a zoo! Yet despite having had a great time there, Yukika looks unhappy...
name: The Letter to Me

description:
Proper Japanese Title: うちの春休み (Uchi no Haruyasumi)

Mesmerized by the cakes of Ichinose, the handsome patissier, Yamato is having a blast at her summer part-time job.
name: My Spring Break

description:
Proper Japanese Title: エリンギ・ブロコビッチ (Eringi Burokobicchi)

Given a one-day reprieve, the boys must again execute a plan to get inside the corrections office, but the Underground Student Council won't make it easy for them. Hana has a personal score that she wishes to settle with Kiyoshi.
name: Eryngii Brockovich

deck: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.
name: Catch and Release

description:
Japanese title: Tsuyoi Yatsu Mikke!! Yōjinbō Rejikku (強いヤツ見っけ!!用心棒レジック)

Original English title: Check It Out, A Tough Guy!! Ledgic, the Body Guard

While hiding from the authorities, Goku, Pan, and Trunks are moved by the cruelties inflicted upon the Imeckians. In the name of justice, they decide to confront Don Kee in a showdown at the Royal Palace!
name: Goku vs. Ledgic

series.name: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic

description:
Japanese title: Tokubetsu Irai. Kininaru Kare ni Chūi Seyo! (特別依頼。気になる彼に注意せよ!)

Lovesick Juvia buys a passion potion with hopes to get her favorite icy guy to warm up to her. When the wrong people catch a whiff, the whole guild gets off on the wrong foot! Meanwhile, Lucy loses her cool when she thinks she’s a fire wizard’s new crush!
name: Special Request: Watch Out for the Guy You Like!

description: Lucy’s dad pays a visit to Magnolia to ask his lovely daughter for a favor, but she doesn’t buy it. When the trade guild her pop is gunning to join is attacked by burglars, Lucy races to save the day.
name: Love & Lucky

description:
Japanese title: Rengōgun, Shūketsu! (連合軍、集結!)

What’s on the menu for the strongest team? Natsu and the gang give service with a smile waiting tables for an old friend. Then, they meet up with former foes and new friends in an alliance to stop a band of evil sorcerers from releasing a dangerous power!
name: Allied Forces, Assemble!

description:
Japanese title: Orashion Seisu Arawaru! (六魔将軍(オラシオンセイス)現る!)

The coalition of conjurers gathers at their meeting place to discuss their plan to stop Oracion Seis. But when the allies are ambushed, the crew get a taste of the evil prowess they’re up against!
name: Enter the Oración Seis!

description:
Japanese title: Tenkū no Miko (天空の巫女)

Things don’t go as planned for the coalition – Oracion Seis steal Wendy and Erza is suffering from a poisonous strike from her showdown with Cobra!
name: Maiden of the Sky

description:
Japanese title: Shōjo to Bōrei (少女と亡霊)

Frightened and conflicted, Wendy is coerced into bringing an evil wizard – whom she remembers fondly – back from the brink of death. Meanwhile, Natsu and Gray are sidelined by some monkey business when a goofy guild stands in their way to save Wendy!
name: The Girl and the Ghost

description:
Japanese title: Deddo Guran Puri (デッドGP(グランプリ))

With Wendy and Carla in tow, Natsu and Gray rush to heal their friend, but they’re sidetrack by an attack from a deceptively quick member of Oracion Seis! Rival ice wizards team up in a high-speed battle to put the brakes on Racer.
name: Dead Grand Prix

description:
Japanese title: Yami (闇)

The sixth member of Oracion Seis finally awakens from his slumber. When Erza is finally back to full strength, she rushes to find Jellal and stop him before he releases the chaotic power of Nirvana!
name: Darkness

description:
Japanese title: Seirei Gassen (星霊合戦)

Lucy goes solo against an identity thief who has her own celestial powers – but she can’t compare when it comes to the coalition member’s compassion for her companions in combat! Nirvana already starts to take effect on the wizards within its radius.
name: Celestial Skirmish

description:
Japanese title: Tsuioku no Jerāru (追憶のジェラール)

As Midnight continues to cut away at the coalition, Erza tracks down Jellal – who has an ulterior motive for awakening the overpowering evil of Nirvana!
name: Jellal of Days Gone By

description:
Japanese title: Hametsu no Kōshin (破滅の行進)

Erza puts her heart into convincing Jellal to cancel the self-destruction spell, but Brain is two steps ahead of them. When Nirvana morphs into an ancient city on legs and targets an unsuspecting guild, Natsu and Happy fight Cobra to try to stop it!
name: March of Destruction

description:
Japanese title:Chōkūchūsen! Natsu vs. Kobura (超空中戦! ナツ vs. コブラ)

As the ancient city of Nirvana continues its path towards Cait Shelter, Natsu and Happy take a pounding from Cobra’s poisonous strikes. But the power of a true dragon slayer should never be underestimated – as long as Happy can keep him off the ground!
name: Super Aerial Battle: Natsu vs. Cobra!

description:
Japanese title:Seiten no Jura (聖十のジュラ)

Jura’s strength is rock solid as he steps up to shut Brain down. Meanwhile, Natsu and Happy are sick as dogs under the effects of Cobra’s poison, and Nirvana’s march has the fire wizard floored – unless some Sky magic can fix him!
name: Wizard Saint Jura

description:
Japanese title: Kimi no Kotoba koso (君の言葉こそ)

There’s still one Oracion Seis member left standing, and Nirvana doesn’t show any signs of stopping! They have to defeat Midnight – and a talking staff?! Erza and Jellal try their hand at cracking the sorcerer’s mirror magic, but things get ugly quick.
name: Your Words

description:
Japanese title: Zero (ゼロ)

Erza uses sheer force and battle smarts to see straight through Midnight’s illusions in a mind-warping fight to the finish. But when the last of the six generals drops, the guild master’s super destructive split personality breaks free!
name: Zero

description:
Japanese title: Tenma kara Yōsei-tachi e (天馬から妖精たちへ)

The members of Cait Shelter brace for impact as Nirvana prepares to fire, but the coalition hasn’t given up hope. There’s only one way to stop it—and one of the wizards will have to cut down Zero singlehandedly to end his evil plan!
name: From Pegasus to Fairies

description:
Japanese title: Omoi no Chikara (想いの力)

The coalition coordinates a team attack to end Nirvana’s course of destruction. But before they can make their final strike, Natsu faces Zero in a fierce battle to the finish! Will an old enemy get in the way, or lend a helping hand?
name: The Power of Feelings

description:
Japanese title: Watashi ga Tsuiteiru (私がついている)

Not even being sent to a land of nothingness can keep the power of the dragon down as Natsu fully unleashes a newfound power! Now the team can attack Nirvana with a unified strike! But what happens when another force comes after their new friends?
name: I'm With You

description:
Japanese title: Tatta Hitori no Tame no Girudo (たった一人の為のギルド)

An ancient guild reveals a dark secret and leaves its only surviving members without a home. Luckily, their new friends are in an awesome guild that loves getting new members!
name: A Guild for One

description:
Japanese title: Ryū no Izanai (竜の誘い)

The coalition parts ways and Fairy Tail welcomes their newest members to the guild! Then, Gray informs Natsu about a lady who claims she met a dragon recently. With hopes of finding their long lost guardian, two Dragon Slayers end up at a creepy hotel.
name: Call of the Dragon

description:
Japanese title: Natsu vs. Gurei!! (ナツ vs. グレイ!!)

Duped by his rival and a strange saleswoman, Natsu finds himself in fiery fisticuffs against a very unlikely foe! Erza and Lucy know something’s up, but they have some scaly copycats to handle before they can help their friend out of a bind!
name: Natsu Vs. Gray

description:
Japanese title:

With Natsu trapped inside her magic-sapping monstrosity, Daphne flies straight for Fairy Tail! As the guild fights to protect Magnolia from annihilation, Makarov gives Gray the third degree.
name: Friendship Overcomes the Dead

description:
Japanese title: Fearī Teiru no Madōshi (フェアリーテイルの魔導士)

The only wizard who can defeat the rampaging Dragonoid is inside the Dragonoid. Since Gray’s plan didn’t pan out like he hoped, Fairy Tail’s only hope is to get Natsu fired up enough to get himself out of the hot seat!
name: A Fairy Tail Wizard

description: Fitz and the team enlist the aid of an Asgardian to unlock the secrets of the ancient monolith that swallowed Simmons, and Agent May is at a crossroads in her personal and professional life.
name: Purpose in the Machine

has_staff_review.name: Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Episode 302: "Purpose in the Machine"

description: Rick don goofed this time and mussed up the whole time frame broh! Beth and Jerry get romantic!
name: A Rickle in Time

description: Morty don tries to save a life in this one broh! Get strapped in broh!
name: Mortynight Run

description: Rick don forgot to check the oil in this one broh. Gotta fix that car in this one broh.
name: The Ricks Must Be Crazy

deck: Second part of Rise of the Villains.
description: Following his reinstatement, Gordon is thrust onto the high-profile case tracking the deadly inmate escape from Arkham Asylum. Meanwhile, Galavan plans his next move, while Bruce enlists the help of his father's old friend to unlock the secrets in his office, and Nygma attempts to ask out Kristin Kringle on a date.
name: Knock, Knock

description: Rick don gets straight emotional in this one broh. Beth and Jerry going ham on each other broh.
name: Auto Erotic Assimilation

description: We don get to meet all sorts of new friends in this one broh. Morty goes ham in this one broh.
name: Total Rickall

description: Rick and Morty don gotta step up and save things in this one broh. A new religion starts up too broh.
name: Get Schwifty

description: Piggy and Kermit deal with the repercussions of their breakup, as the pressure of running Piggy's show bares down on Kermit. Meanwhile Fozzy tries to impress his girlfriends parents.
name: Pig Girls Don't Cry

description: Rick don joins in on some hijinks in this one broh. Beth and Jerry sort out their relationship too broh.
name: Big Trouble In Little Sanchez

description: Things going ham in this one broh. Jerry gots all sick and Rick sparks up the TV broh.
name: Interdimensional Cable 2: Tempting Fate

description: Morty goofs this time broh and now they gotta chill out and wait. Jerry and Summer explore their father daughter relationship too broh.
name: Look Who's Purging Now

description: When Kermit sets Piggy up with a new boyfriend she suddenly becomes nice leaving the Muppets split on on her new personality while Kermit trying to tear them apart. Meanwhile Fozzie steals from Jay Leno and Bobo the Bear tries to sell is daughter's girl scout cookies.
name: Hostile Makeover

description: The original pitch video for the series that was the basis for the new show.
name: First Look Presentation

description: Eph must choose between Zack's safety and the safety of the citizens of NYC. Meanwhile, his relationship with Nora reaches a critical impasse, and Gus and Angel assemble an unlikely gang of Sun-hunters.
name: Fallen Light

description: The National Guard's plan for the neightborhood and its residents is revealed, forcing Travis and Madison to make a difficult decision.
name: Cobalt

description: Stewie is diagnosed with ADD and prescribed Adderall, which Brian takes to write a 2000-page proposal to pitch to author George R.R. Martin at a book convention. Meanwhile, Quagmire and Peter compete, Iron Chef-style, to determine which of them gets to keep his new cooking show.
name: Pilling Them Softly

description: For Father's Day, the guys track down Joe's estranged father. But when Joe explains that his dad is intolerant of people with disabilities, Peter steps in and pretends to be Joe. Meanwhile, Stewie's doctor tells him that he'll only grow to be 5'1", so he hangs out with Tiny Tom Cruise to understand what it's like to be short.
name: Papa Has A Rollin' Son

description: Daisy, Mack and Coulson race to protect Lincoln as Rosalind’s team hunts down the Inhuman in their quest for powered people. Meanwhile, Hunter proves that there is no line that he will not cross to exact his revenge against Ward and HYDRA.
name: A Wanted (Inhu)man
